X|\lambda \sim Poisson (\lambda)
\lambda \sim  Gamma(shape = r, scale = p/(1 â p))
NB(r,p)
var(X) = \frac{pr}{(1-p)^2}
E(X) = \frac{pr}{1-p}
var(\lambda) = r \cdot \frac{p}{1-p}
var(\lambda) = var(X) - E(X) = \frac{pr}{(1-p)^2} - \frac{pr}{1-p} = \frac{rp}{1-p}
\lambda
Var(X) = E(Var(X|\lambda))+ Var(E(X|\lambda))
Var(X) = E(\lambda)+ Var(\lambda)
Var(\lambda) = Var(X) - E(\lambda)
E(X) = E(E(X|\lambda)) = E(\lambda)
\mu
var(X) = \mu + \mu^2/size
var(\lambda) = \mu^2/size
